<paragraph id="8BD336B3FFE7F956FF6BFD4C6757FC9C" blockId="35.[151,1436,540,1104]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FFE7F956FF6BFD4C6741FD0C" bold="true" box="[199,308,684,709]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Remarks</emphasis>
. The specimens at hand appear to be more similar to the subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D30FFE7F956FBE0FD4D63E2FD0D" authority="Payne &amp; Allen, 1991" authorityName="Payne &amp; Allen" authorityYear="1991" box="[1100,1431,684,709]" class="Gastropoda" family="Diaphanidae" genus="Diaphana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FFE7F956FBE0FD4D62EFFD0D" box="[1100,1178,685,708]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">minuta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B42FFE7F956FB0FFD4D63E2FD0D" author="Payne" box="[1187,1431,684,709]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refString="Payne, C. M. &amp; Allen, J. A. (1991) The morphology of deep-sea Thyasiridae (Mollusca: Bivalvia) from the Atlantic Ocean. Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London, B, 334, 481 - 562. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1098 / rstb. 1991.0128" type="journal article" year="1991">Payne &amp; Allen, 1991</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, than to the nominal species of Jeffreys, in having an oval (not subtriangular) shell with rounded (not wedgeshaped) posterior angulation. We follow 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B42FFE7F956FDCDFD146515FCC4" author="Oliver" box="[609,864,756,781]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refString="Oliver, P. G. &amp; Levin, L. (2006) A new species of the family Thyasiridae (Mollusca: Bivalvia) from the oxygen minimum zone of the Pakistan margin. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 86, 411 - 416. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1017 / s 0025315406013270" type="journal article" year="2006">Oliver &amp; Levin (2006)</bibRefCitation>
in preferring the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D30FFE7F956FBC1FD1566BAFCF9" authority="Verrill &amp; Bush, 1898" authorityName="Verrill &amp; Bush" authorityYear="1898" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Leptaxinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FFE7F956FBC1FD15629DFCC5" box="[1133,1256,757,780]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Leptaxinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B42FFE7F956FB43FD1466BAFCF9" author="Verrill" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refString="Verrill, A. E. &amp; Bush, K. J. (1898) Revision of the deep-water Mollusca of the Atlantic coast of North America, with descriptions of new genera and species. Part I. - Bivalvia. Proceedings U. S. National Museum, 20 (1139), 775 - 901. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.20 - 1139.775" type="journal article" year="1898">Verrill &amp; Bush, 1898</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
for the present taxon, rather than 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D30FFE7F956FDF7FCF76502FCF9" authority="Lamarck, 1818" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1818" box="[603,887,791,816]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Thyasira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FFE7F956FDF7FCF764CAFCF9" box="[603,703,791,816]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Thyasira</emphasis>
Lamarck, 1818
</taxonomicName>
, for the presence of both cardinal tubercles and lateral teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD336B3FFE7F956FF6BFCBF6781FC55" blockId="35.[151,1436,540,1104]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FFE7F956FF6BFCBF6726FCB1" bold="true" box="[199,339,863,888]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Occurrence</emphasis>
. Box-corer samples BC10 (2 specimens), BC66 (2), BC67 (3), BC72 (5); cores BC21 (1), BC72 (5). Maximum length: 
<quantity id="4C949B56FFE7F956FE3AFC64679AFC55" box="[406,495,900,925]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3766538FFE7F956FF6BFC476523FB99" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD336B3FFE7F956FF6BFC4767FEFBE4" blockId="35.[151,1436,540,1104]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FFE7F956FF6BFC47679CFC09" bold="true" box="[199,489,935,960]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D30FFE7F956FE5BFC49649CFC09" box="[503,745,935,960]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Leptaxinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subovatus">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FFE7F956FE5BFC49649CFC09" box="[503,745,935,960]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Leptaxinus subovatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed troughout the Atlantic, from 
<collectingCountry id="F37B7623FFE7F956FB65FC47636EFC09" box="[1225,1307,935,960]" name="Iceland" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Iceland</collectingCountry>
and Faroes to 
<collectingCountry id="F37B7623FFE7F956FF14FC2C6737FC2C" box="[184,322,972,997]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<collectingRegion id="49A8F851FFE7F956FF14FC2C6687FC2D" box="[184,242,972,996]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Cape</collectingRegion>
Verde
</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37B7623FFE7F956FEFEFC2C67D0FC2C" box="[338,421,972,997]" name="Angola" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Angola</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F37B7623FFE7F956FE49FC2C6422FC2C" box="[485,599,972,997]" name="Argentina" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, and in the Mediterranean; it is found in the 
<quantity id="4C949B56FFE7F956FBD5FC2C637EFC2D" box="[1145,1291,972,996]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="m" value="2100.0" valueMax="4000.0" valueMin="200.0">200–4000 m</quantity>
bathymetric interval, reaching shallower depths at arctic latitudes (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B42FFE7F956FD50FC10659CFBC1" author="Payne" box="[764,1001,1007,1032]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refString="Payne, C. M. &amp; Allen, J. A. (1991) The morphology of deep-sea Thyasiridae (Mollusca: Bivalvia) from the Atlantic Ocean. Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London, B, 334, 481 - 562. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1098 / rstb. 1991.0128" type="journal article" year="1991">Payne &amp; Allen 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B42FFE7F956FC5AFC1062A8FBC1" author="Poppe" box="[1014,1245,1008,1032]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refString="Poppe, G. T. &amp; Goto, Y. (1993) European Seashells. Volume II. (Scaphopoda, Bivalvia, Cephalopoda). Verlag Christa Hemmen, Wiesbaden, 221 pp." type="book" year="1993">
Poppe &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="49A8F851FFE7F956FBCEFC1062EFFBC1" box="[1122,1178,1008,1032]" country="Malta" name="Zebbug" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Goto</collectingRegion>
1993
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B42FFE7F956FB46FC0F6683FBE5" author="Di" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refString="Di Geronimo, I., Rosso, A., La Perna, R. &amp; Sanfilippo, R. (2001) Deep-sea (250 - 1,550 m) Benthic Thanatocoenoses from Southern Thyrrenian Sea. In: Faranda, F. M., Guglielmo, L., Spezie, G. (Eds), Mediterranean Ecosystems - Structures and Processes, Springer, Milano, pp. 277 - 288. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 88 - 470 - 2105 - 1 _ 36" type="book chapter" year="2001">
Di Geronimo 
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FFE7F956FA24FC1166C1FBE4" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B42FFE7F956FEADFBF4670AFBE4" author="Sneli" box="[257,383,1044,1069]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refString="Sneli, J. - A. (2005) Amphi-Atlantic distribution of marine Mollusca based on the results of the BIOFAR investigations. BIOFAR Proceedings, 2005, 88 - 93." type="book chapter" year="2005">Sneli 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD336B3FFE7F956FF6BFBD76523FB99" blockId="35.[151,1436,540,1104]" box="[199,854,1079,1104]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
